What a whirlwind it has been so far! Humbled by the wonderful people in my life who have supported and continue to support me on this creative journey. 

This is my first one woman production and I am enjoyed every wild, frenzied, exhilarated moment. With the support of my fellow performers within Soho Theatre, my entry into the live performance circuit has been one of unity, joy, and celebration. Meeting Phoebe Waller-Bridge was a highlight of my first night up in Edinburgh, along with the captivating, evocative performance from @legateauchocolat ♥️ 

Adopting an Alan Bennett style, ‘Talking Heads’ formula, I dedicate segments of the play to the many characters we have had to fashion and harness in our lives.

From cabaret and comedy, to issues of mental health, societal perceptions and gender, this work-in-progress show develops excitedly with every evening performance. (With updates and more to follow, I pose a question for potential pondering… who hasn’t been a naughty chops? 💫 

My final show will fall on the eve of Sat 12th in which I’ll be announcing some thrilling news. 🥳

A huge thank you to those who supported and donated towards this artistic endeavour. Never did I think I’d be bringing a show like this to @edfringe 

Tickets 
5th to the 12th August 🎭 🎙️ 🥂
https://tickets.edfringe.com/whats-on/who-s-been-a-naughty-chops

All my love and wallops, 

Lady Wentworth

🎉Thank you @sohotheatre (and to Lee Griffiths) for your guidance, training and support. ♥️ 🎉 @edfringe is unlike any experience I’ve ever encountered before and a great tread in the right direction. 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿 🎭 🎙️ 

I feel honoured to share a poster with such talented individuals, comics, thespians and more. To head up to Scotland alone would be a solitary journey, therefore I am incredibly grateful to have such a supportive network of fellow performers. (Forgive me if I’ve missed anyone). 

I’ll be at @paradisegreenuk for my final two shows! The staff and team at the venue have been wonderful and so accommodating. What a great team to have as I leap straight in at the deep end! My venue has been perfect in showcasing the narrative.

Who’s Been a Naughty Chops? (Wonderful to meet you, Phoebe Waller-Bridge). ♥️ #fleabag

Welcome to my debut performance and entry into the fabulous festival that is Edinburgh Fringe. It would be an understatement to say that this experience has been instrumental in moving mountains for me already… 💫

I’ll see you at the Annexe this evening. Come with an open mind, a willingness to embrace the world of kink; and perhaps a tissue or two. 🎭 I’ll see you amidst the sultry, billowing haze.

WOW!! What a night!!!!! 🌟🌟🌟

What a turnout! Thank you to @sohotheatre for supporting me this evening in the audience. It’s been an exhilarating few days and tonight was a wonderful finale! 🎉 I LOVED every second of this ‘work in progress’ show that has been excitedly developing every evening! 

I was stunned at the attendance this evening! Thank you for all the kind words; the lovely comments and the encouragement. I feel I am at the very beginning of my journey and can’t wait to see how this develops. Thank you to Shaz (Soho Theatre) and to the Lee Griffiths (Soho Theatre) as embarking upon the Fringe without your guidance would have been a solitary path to tread. 

The catalyst for this show was due to the passing of a friend. I only knew in May that I was committing to such an empowering project and I am humbled by the messages I have received, the plane journeys up here to see me, and the kind gifts given after performances. 

Thank you to @thomas_technician for helping me address the nuances of my performance and for bringing it to life! @minecerciofficial & @alex.igbanoi for your contribution. Thank you to @tomtheclutz for being there for me and for @paradisegreenuk for your outstanding expertise and warm welcome. 

My theatrical counsel @bridget.k.quinn - without you, nothing is possible. @edfringe  I shall be back next year with a smile, a tale, a tissue, and a giggle. 

@adammcgee_ @sallysquiggles @_.reece your voiceovers really are enhanced my narrative. 🙏🏼♥️

I will see you at my post-Fringe; London show! 📍 🇬🇧 

Love and wallops. This has bloody well changed my life!! 

Lady Wentworth
